The paper introduces an algorithm for generating optimal plans in a Markov Decision Process (MDP), which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The algorithm uses Particle Swarm Optimization, which is a technique commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of the algorithm as a model-predictive controller (MPC), which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the algorithm through statistical analysis, which is a common technique in statistics and machine learning (cs.SI).
